videos.description: Bruce Brown finds Dejan Vasiljevic for the transition lay-in following the Kamari Murphy steal.
videos.headline: Stingy defense by Miami leads to a transition layup

videos.description: Miami guard Ja'Quan Newton finds Kamari Murphy with the alley-oop to give the Hurricanes the lead.
videos.headline: Murphy with the alley-oop slam for Miami

videos.description: Davon Reed drives the lane and gets the tough layup, plus the foul.
videos.headline: Reed gets the and-1 to go for the Hurricanes

videos.description: Hokies guard Ahmed Hill intercepts the pass and takes it the other way for two.
videos.headline: Hill comes up big for Virginia Tech with the steal and lay-in

videos.description: Miami guard Anthony Lawrence Jr. drives and passes to Kamari Murphy for the slam.
videos.headline: Murphy's dunk ties the game in the 2nd half

videos.description: Virginia Tech guard Ty Outlaw nails his eighth three pointer of the night to put the Hokies up   by four late.
videos.headline: Outlaw increases Hokies lead late with big 3-pointer

videos.description: Hokies guard Justin Robinson comes up huge as he intercepts the inbound pass to solidify the win against Miami.
videos.headline: Robinson's late steal seals the victory for Virginia Tech

videos.description: Doug Sherman and LaPhonso Ellis discuss Ty Outlaw and Seth Allen's night as Virginia Tech defeats No. 25 Miami.
videos.headline: Postgame breakdown: Miami at Virginia Tech
